        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4780582" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17122842692044055482">So many people love this series. Not sure why. The hero is a leperous (no, not lecherous) rapist and incredibly whiny. The bad guy is named Lord Foul, ferchissakes. I hated everything about the first few chapters of this book. Once the main character forced himself on a girl, and then the author tried to make it a sympathetic moment (for the perpetrator), I hurled it at the wall in disgust and never finished reading it. <br/><br/>Right around the same level of arrogant sexist manhood as Piers Anthony.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


